Route Waiting period
Conviction for conduct no longer criminal After sentence/supervision complete and restitution/surcharges paid
Qualifying misdemeanor conviction 3 years after sentence completion
Qualifying felony conviction 7 years after sentence completion
Qualifying DUI misdemeanor 10 years after sentence completion
No probable cause / dismissal / acquittal Court should seal within 60 days after final disposition unless objection
Prosecutor stipulation for non-conviction Any time
Petition for non-conviction sealing Any time, if interests of justice support it
Age 18-21 qualifying crime 30 days after sentence completion
Offense committed before age 25 2 years after final discharge, plus 10-year listed-crime clean period
Juvenile delinquency Generally 2 years after final discharge
Denied petition Wait 2 years unless court allows shorter period
17. Wilma
do not say eligible unless&
rules
Wilma should not say
you are eligible
unless these are confirmed:
For adult expungement

the conviction is for conduct no longer criminal;
sentence/supervision is complete;
restitution and surcharges are paid or waived;
exact statute and facts match current law.
For adult misdemeanor sealing
offense is not excluded from qualifying-crime definition;
3 years have passed since sentence completion;
restitution/surcharges are paid or waived;
no pending charge blocks court action.
For adult felony sealing
exact felony is on Vermonts qualifying list or unconditional pardon applies;
7 years have passed since sentence completion;
restitution/surcharges are paid or waived;
no pending charge blocks court action.
For DUI sealing
10 years have passed since sentence completion;
no CDL/commercial permit;
restitution/surcharges paid or waived;
if offense was before age 25, under-25 route checked.
For under-25 sealing
offense date before 25th birthday;
2 years since final discharge;
no listed-crime conviction/adjudication in prior 10 years;
no pending listed-crime proceeding;
rehabilitation evidence available.
For non-convictions
disposition confirmed: no probable cause, dismissal before trial, or acquittal;
60-day automatic-sealing window checked;
if older/unsealed, petition or stipulation route used.
